{"STOW":[{"def":"To place or arrange in a compact mass; to put in its proper place, or in a suitable place; to pack; as, to stowbags, bales, or casks in a ship's hold; to stow hay in a mow; to stow sheaves.","pos":""},{"def":"To put away in some place; to hide; to lodge.","pos":""}],"STOWAGE":[{"def":"The act or method of stowing; as, the stowage of provisions in a vessel.","pos":""},{"def":"Room in which things may be stowed.","pos":""}],"STOWAWAY":[{"def":"One who conceals himself board of a vessel about to leave port, or on a railway train, in order to obtain a free passage.","pos":""}],"STOWBOARD":[{"def":"A place into which rubbish is put.","pos":""}],"STOWING":[{"def":"A method of working in which the waste is packed into the space formed by excavating the vein.","pos":""}]}